p/5152x5152+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd4%2Ff2%2Fa57bd5b8430289e38ddbca7c7e9f%2Fgeneral-press.png" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/png" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5152x5152+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd4%2Ff2%2Fa57bd5b8430289e38ddbca7c7e9f%2Fgeneral-press.png" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5152x5152+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd4%2Ff2%2Fa57bd5b8430289e38ddbca7c7e9f%2Fgeneral-press.png" class="img" alt="Yebba&amp;#039;s song &amp;quot;Yellow Eyes&amp;quot; is one of our critics&amp;#039; favorite songs of the year." fetchpriority="high" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Yebba's song "Yellow Eyes" is one of our critics' favorite songs of the year.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Charles Myers/RCA                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;When it comes to music, the concept of "best" might be a lie, but our love stays true. The 24 albums and songs on you'll find on this page are our most fervent answers to the question we probably get asked most often, by friends and family and new acquaintances alike: What should I listen to? &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In celebration of the mid-point of the year and in an effort to spread the love, a dozen members of NPR Music's team — podcast hosts, critics and editors — each distilled their affections down to one song and one album from the first half of 2026. These are our highest recommendations.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Want more stories like this? &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/music" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Get the NPR Music newsletter,&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; sent weekly.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h2 class="edTag"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;No. 1 Albums of 2026 (So Far)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-131170" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 1000;         --source-height: 1000;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x1000+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F10%2Fc1207b7d4f06b6a8f7615981983c%2Fmon-cover-3000x3000-rgb-2.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x1000+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F10%2Fc1207b7d4f06b6a8f7615981983c%2Fmon-cover-3000x3000-rgb-2.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x1000+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F10%2Fc1207b7d4f06b6a8f7615981983c%2Fmon-cover-3000x3000-rgb-2.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x1000+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F10%2Fc1207b7d4f06b6a8f7615981983c%2Fmon-cover-3000x3000-rgb-2.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspo